    <h1>Sending newsletters</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This page of the manual describes which settings you need to carry out to send newsletters with plentymarkets. Send your newsletters e.g. with the <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#100">newsletter service integrated in plentymarkets</a>, via the integrated interface to <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#1700">CleverReach</a> or via other email marketing and newsletter plugins available in the <a href="https://marketplace.plentymarkets.com/en/plugins/integration" target="_blank" rel="noopener">plentyMarketplace</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Setting up the newsletter service integrated in plentymarkets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the following sub-chapters, you will learn how to set up the newsletter service that is integrated in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Double opt-in method</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The double opt-in method is used in plentymarkets. This means that the recipient is sent an email after having asked to receive the newsletter. This email contains a link that is used to confirm the newsletter subscription. Only after the customer has clicked on the link is the customer registered for the newsletter. This method is integrated in plentymarkets and cannot be changed.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="200">1.1. Entering newsletter login details</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Client</strong> » <em>Select client</em> » <strong>Email » Newsletter</strong>. Enter the login details to use the newsletter service that is integrated in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Entering newsletter login details:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Client</strong> » <em>Select client</em> » <strong>Email » Newsletter</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-newsletter-login-details">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
